******
[2]
Date: Sun 13 Feb 2022 15:43 GMT
Source: Al Akhbar [in Arabic, trans., edited]
http://alakhbar.info/?q=node/38449


Director-General of Public Health, Dr Mohamed Mahmoud Ould Eel Mahmoud, during a press conference said the Ministry of Health announced on Sunday [13 Feb 2022], the registration of 2 cases of Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever during the past days, one of them in a Nouakchott hospital, and the other inside the country.

The Director-General of Public Health said that one of 2 two cases was discovered in a Nouakchott hospital and that the 2nd case was in a hospital inside, without specifying the location.

In a clarification published by the Ministry of Health on its Facebook page, Ould Eel Mahmoud confirmed that the 2 cases came from the same area, which is a pastoral area in one of the governorates of the interior.

Ould Eel Mahmoud warned that this disease is one of the endemic diseases in West Africa and that one or 2 cases are discovered annually in Mauritania, usually in people whose jobs require them to mix with animals.

Ould Eel Mahmoud said that the ministry issued to health centers and points an order to be vigilant and monitor the health situation, and to alert citizens to be careful.

Ould Eel Mahmoud added that the ministry announced the discovery of the 2 cases, and the measures taken "in line with the ministry's strategy to expose citizens to all developments related to public health."

Ould Eel Mahmoud reassured citizens about this fever, adding that joint missions were dispatched between the ministry and the Ministry of Animal Development to monitor the situation, isolate suspected animals, search for other possible cases, and take the necessary measures in a timely manner.

